<paragraph id="IAS23_4"><paranum>4</paranum><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS 23"/><data name="paranum" value="4"/></prolog><body><variant base="F32828864" id="IAS23_4_V2" principles="no"> <p id="IAS23_P0013">An entity is not required to apply the Standard to <xref base="F3101210" href="IAS23_5.dita#IAS23_5/IAS23_P0019">borrowing costs<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0023"/></ph></xref> directly attributable to the acquisition, construction or production of: </p> <ol base="F32828866" id="IAS23_L0002" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p base="F32828868" id="IAS23_P0014">a <xref base="F3101211" href="IAS23_5.dita#IAS23_5/IAS23_P0020">qualifying asset<ph outputclass="def_xref"><xref keyref="GLOSSARY_DI0311"/></ph></xref> measured at fair value, for example a biological asset within the scope of <xref base="F35109244" href="../ias41/IAS41_TOC.dita#IAS41_TOC0001/IAS41_TOC0001_V2" id="IAS23_X0034"><ph outputclass="standard_ref"><ph outputclass="standard_number">IAS 41</ph> <ph outputclass="standard_title">Agriculture</ph></ph></xref>; or</p> </li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p base="F32828875" id="IAS23_P0016">inventories that are manufactured, or otherwise produced, in large quantities on a repetitive basis.</p> </li></ol></variant></body></paragraph>